\section{Design}
\label{ch:design}

This chapter specifies the design of \textit{Skillens}, a data-driven personalised educational content recommender aligned with \textbf{Project Template 1 (CM3005 Data Science), Idea 1.1}. The design is written with a strict traceability goal: every design element described here corresponds to an implemented component in the submitted repository, and all evaluation-critical decisions (especially data splitting and leakage prevention) are described as design constraints rather than informal intentions.

At a high level, Skillens is built around three principles:

\begin{enumerate}
  \item \textbf{Cold-start usability:} the system must produce meaningful recommendations when the learner has little or no interaction history (e.g.\ cold start).
  \item \textbf{Hybrid relevance:} when interaction history exists, collaborative signals should complement content similarity rather than replace it.
  \item \textbf{Transparent outputs:} the interface should provide clear, bounded explanations that describe model behaviour without implying pedagogical causality.
\end{enumerate}

Figure~\ref{fig:end_to_end_workflow} provides the end-to-end workflow that the remainder of this chapter formalises.

