\section{Evaluation}

In this chapter, complete evaluation results on Skillens on OULAD are provided. The evaluation criteria include accuracy, diversity, fairness, and statistical rigor. All the results are based on the test set and have used user-wise temporal splits to avoid leakage in the data.

\subsection{Evaluation methodology}

The evaluation uses per-user temporal splits to ensure realistic deployment scenarios. For each user, interactions are sorted by timestamp and split into train (60\%), validation (20\%), and test (20\%) sets. This ensures that training interactions always precede test interactions, preventing temporal leakage.

The evaluation protocol follows these steps:
\begin{enumerate}
  \item For each user in the test set, build a goal query from their training interactions
  \item Generate top-$K$ recommendations using the trained model
  \item Compare recommendations against held-out test interactions
  \item Compute metrics per user, then aggregate across all users
\end{enumerate}

Metrics are computed with 95\% bootstrap confidence intervals to quantify uncertainty. Statistical significance testing uses paired t-tests and Wilcoxon signed-rank tests with Bonferroni correction for multiple comparisons.

