Key limitations include:
\begin{itemize}
  \item ItemKNN performs poorly due to extreme sparsity, limiting collaborative filtering benefits
  \item Fairness gaps persist across demographic groups despite mitigation efforts
  \item Absolute performance is constrained by OULAD's sparse interaction patterns
  \item Offline evaluation cannot measure actual learning impact or user satisfaction
\end{itemize}

The findings of the evaluation show that both content-based filtering and collaborative filtering contribute positively to educational recommendation, even under extreme sparsity. The hybrid approach combines both signals effectively: it achieved 49.2\% improvement over popularity baselines with no loss in diversity and coverage.

